51.9	Gloria_Swanson	Gloria Swanson	Gloria Swanson (March 27, 1899 â€“ April 4, 1983) was an American actress, singer and producer. She was one of the most prominent stars during the silent film era as both an actress and a fashion icon, especially under the direction of Cecil B. DeMille, made dozens of silents and was nominated for the first Academy Award in the Best Actress category. She had also produced her own films such as the controversial Sadie Thompson and The Love of Sunya. In 1929, Swanson successfully transitioned to talkies with The Trespasser.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b5/Swanson-portrait.jpg/220px-Swanson-portrait.jpg
